{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17412763","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17412763"},"attributes":{"position":1,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T07:38:52+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T07:38:52+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261074"}},"session":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261074"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16910"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17563873","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17563873"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:06:04+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:06:04+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16910"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261074","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionSessions/1261074"},"attributes":{"startedAt":"2025-09-28T07:38:50+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-28T07:40:20+09:30","sessionType":"qbank","questionStatus":"all","difficulty":[],"timeLimit":null,"questionCount":19,"questionsAnswered":7,"marksTotal":19,"marksAttainable":7,"marksAttempted":7,"finishedAt":"2025-09-28T07:39:59+09:30","resultsAvailable":true,"score":0.14,"questionsCorrect":1,"marksCorrect":1},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"pack":{"data":{"type":"packs","id":"5"}},"exam":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questions","id":"16910","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16910"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.07,0.75,0.01,0.03,0.14]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9600"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67661"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9600","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9600"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16910"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53117"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"22"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"2320"},{"type":"tags","id":"3891"},{"type":"tags","id":"4540"},{"type":"tags","id":"4985"},{"type":"tags","id":"11137"},{"type":"tags","id":"11139"},{"type":"tags","id":"11426"},{"type":"tags","id":"11634"},{"type":"tags","id":"12799"},{"type":"tags","id":"12804"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22667"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43665"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67661","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/67661"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 25-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic seeking preconception advice. She was diagnosed with a bicornuate uterus on hysterosalpingogram two years ago during investigation of heavy menstrual bleeding. She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. She reports regular menstrual cycles every 28 days. She has never been pregnant before. On examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most accurate regarding her fertility and pregnancy outcomes?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Natural conception is unlikely without surgical correction","Natural conception is likely but pregnancy complications are more common","In vitro fertilisation is required for conception","Caesarean section is mandatory for delivery","Infertility is much more common due to the anomaly"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient has a known bicornuate uterus and is seeking advice about conception and pregnancy. Understanding the implications of this anatomical variation is crucial for appropriate counselling.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENatural conception is likely but pregnancy complications are more common\u003C/strong\u003E is the most accurate statement. Women with bicornuate uterus typically have normal fertility and can conceive naturally. However, they have an increased risk of pregnancy complications including first and second trimester miscarriage (25-30%), preterm delivery (15-25%), and malpresentation (20-30%).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENatural conception is unlikely without surgical correction\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. Surgical correction (metroplasty) is rarely indicated for bicornuate uterus as fertility is usually unaffected. Surgery may be considered in cases of recurrent pregnancy loss.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIn vitro fertilisation is required for conception\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. Women with bicornuate uterus typically have normal fertility and can conceive naturally. IVF would only be indicated if there were other fertility factors present.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECaesarean section is mandatory for delivery\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. While the caesarean section rate is higher in women with bicornuate uterus due to increased risk of malpresentation, vaginal delivery is still possible and should be considered if the fetus is in cephalic presentation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInfertility is much more common\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. Women with bicornuate uterus typically have normal fertility rates comparable to the general population. The main concerns relate to pregnancy complications rather than conception difficulties.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe key to managing pregnancy in women with bicornuate uterus is close antenatal monitoring, particularly for cervical length and fetal growth. Serial ultrasound scans are typically performed to monitor these parameters. Women should be counselled about the signs and symptoms of preterm labour.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Bicornuate uterus does not typically affect fertility or ability to conceive naturally","Bicornuate uterus increases risk of pregnancy complications including miscarriage, preterm birth, and malpresentation","Women with bicornuate uterus require close antenatal monitoring during pregnancy"],"references":["Akhtar MA, Saravelos SH, Li TC, Jayaprakasan K; on behalf of the Royal College of Obstetricians and Gynaecologists. Reproductive implications and management of congenital uterine anomalies. Scientific Impact Paper No. 62. BJOG. 2019 Nov 20; DOI: 10.1111/1471-0528.15968.","Jayaprakasan K, Ojha K. Diagnosis of Congenital Uterine Abnormalities: Practical Considerations. J Clin Med. 2022 Feb 25;11(5):1251. doi: 10.3390/jcm11051251. PMID: 35268343; PMCID: PMC8911320."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53117"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16910"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53117","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/53117"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-06T14:01:09+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-06T14:02:13+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9600"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67661"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"22","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/22"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf53","name":"Gynaecology","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"3"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"64","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/64"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","na